<TITLE> Telenor CFO to jump ship </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Falun, Sept 21 (bdnews24.com) - Chief financial officer Trond Westlie will leave Norway's Telenor, majority owner of Grameenphone, to take up the same position in A. P. Moeller-Maersk Group at the end of the year. Telenorwhich holds a 62 percent share of GP, the leading mobile phone operator in Bangladeshin a statement on Monday said Westlie will leave on December 31 2009. "Telenor is one of the most exciting companies for a CFO in Norway. Only a few, if any, Norwegian companies can demonstrate an equally successful international expansion," said Westlie. "The decision to leave the company was therefore not an easy one to make. However, the challenges and opportunities at Maersk are too exciting to resist," he said. "It's not with a light heart we see him go  I consider him one of the leading CFOs in Norway, as well as being a profiled manager in Telenor and a valuable advisor," said Telenor President and CEO Jon Fredrik Baksaas. Westlie has worked at Telenor for five years. During this period, the company has experienced significant growth, and the number of mobile subscriptions has grown with approximately 100 million, Telenor said. The Norwegian telecoms giant said it will immediately begin the search for his successor
